Overview

Rana Radiansyah

ID# 1765471

PSYCH 403

The Sedimentation of Cognitive States

This work is inspired by research and first-person accounts of synesthesia, in which

sensory modalities, sound, color, and spatial perception are experienced as intrinsically

interconnected. This perception challenges dominant models of cognition that prioritize

separation between sensory channels, instead suggesting that perception operates as a layered

process shaped by memory and affect. The visual language is further inspired by the "tesseract"

sequence in Interstellar (2014), where time collapses into a spatial dimension. In this piece,

memories are not fixed recollections but immersive, embodied phenomena encountered within a

non-linear architecture. Designed as an interactive, painterly installation, the work translates

real-time brainwave activity, associated with attentional states, relaxation, and cognitive

engagement, into evolving visual and auditory forms. Rather than functioning as a diagnostic or

representational interface, the system emphasizes temporal accumulation and persistence,

reflecting how neural activity unfolds continuously and how cognitive states leave residual traces

over time. Visual elements are layered and retained, evoking processes of memory consolidation

and neural plasticity, while sound operates as a subtle, parallel channel that reinforces

cross-modal integration. By situating viewers within a responsive environment that externalizes

internal neural dynamics, the work invites participants to experience cognition as a spatial and

sensory phenomenon, foregrounding the relationship between perception, memory, and

embodied awareness within a shared gallery context.

In translating these concepts into a generative installation, the work faces the significant

challenge of visual continuity. While the simulated brainwave data is often erratic and discrete,

the goal of this piece is to achieve smooth, painterly transitions that mirror the fluid nature of

consciousness. This requires moving beyond reactive "data visualization" toward a system where

every change feels organic and intentional. While entirely using the simulated data from the

software, I am trying to refine the ways in which these digital marks can flow into one another

without interruption, ensuring that the viewer perceives a "stream" of consciousness rather than a

series of disconnected data points. A second critical challenge lies in the spatial organization of

---

time. To visualize the way mental states "sediment" within the mind, the system must precisely

align the animation of brainwaves as they update frame-by-frame. By layering these waves from

left to right, the installation creates a persistent record of the immediate past. Solving the

alignment of these accumulating ribbons is essential to the work's metaphor, that it allows users

to see their own cognitive history as a living, spatialized canvas.

By merging neuroscience, generative sound, and painterly aesthetics, the piece seeks to

externalize the invisible textures of thought. It offers a momentary encounter with one‚Äôs own

mental processes, not through representational accuracy, but through a shared, sensorial

experience that resists full predictability.

// Brainwave Living Painterly EEG ‚Äì Indigo Theta (Micro Background) + Soft Delta + Sound

let ribbons = [];

let synth;

let lastEventTime = 0;

// ------------------- Bands -------------------

const bands = ['delta', 'theta', 'alpha', 'beta', 'gamma'];

let bandColors = {

delta: { h: 30, s: 60, b: 90 },

theta: { h: 265, s: 40, b: 85 },

alpha: { h: 320, s: 70, b: 90 },

beta: { h: 210, s: 80, b: 90 },

gamma: { h: 0, s: 0, b: 100 }

---

};

function setup() {

colorMode(HSB, 360, 100, 100, 1);

background(0);

synth = new p5.PolySynth();

if (!window.eegData) {

window.eegData = {

connected: false,

simulating: true,

alpha: 0.5,

beta: 0.5,

theta: 0.5,

delta: 0.5,

gamma: 0.5,

meditation: 0.5,

attention: 0.5

};

}

}

function draw() {

// painterly fade

noStroke();

fill(0, 0, 0, 0.02);

rect(0, 0, width, height);

let interval = map(eegData.attention, 0, 1, 1000, 240);

if (millis() - lastEventTime > interval) {

---

createRibbon();

playBrainSound();

lastEventTime = millis();

}

for (let r of ribbons) {

updateRibbon(r);

drawRibbon(r);

}

drawHUD();

}

// ------------------- Ribbon Creation -------------------

function createRibbon() {

let ribbon = { ribbons: {} };

ribbon.ribbons.alpha = makeWave('alpha', height * 0.9);

ribbon.ribbons.beta = makeWave('beta', 80);

ribbon.ribbons.gamma = makeWave('gamma', 200);

// THETA ‚Äî VERY SMALL, BACKGROUND TEXTURE

ribbon.ribbons.theta = {

x: random(width),

y: random(height),

size: map(eegData.theta, 0, 1, 18, 45), // <<< WAY SMALLER

hue: bandColors.theta.h,

alpha: map(eegData.theta, 0, 1, 0.04, 0.1),

offsetX: random(1000),

offsetY: random(2000),

wobbleX: random(3, 8),

---

wobbleY: random(3, 8)

};

// Delta ‚Äì soft atmospheric mist

ribbon.ribbons.delta = {

x: random(width),

y: random(height),

hue: bandColors.delta.h,

alpha: map(eegData.delta, 0, 1, 0.03, 0.12),

offsetX: random(1000),

offsetY: random(2000)

};

ribbons.push(ribbon);

if (ribbons.length > 260) ribbons.shift();

}

function makeWave(band, ampMax) {

return {

x: random(width),

y: random(height),

length: random(100, 300),

amplitude: map(eegData[band], 0, 1, 30, ampMax),

frequency: map(eegData[band], 0, 1, 0.004, 0.02),

hue: bandColors[band].h,

alpha: map(eegData[band], 0, 1, 0.2, 0.55),

strokeWeight: map(eegData[band], 0, 1, 1, 10),

offsetX: random(1000),

offsetY: random(2000)

};

}

---

// ------------------- Update -------------------

function updateRibbon(r) {

for (let k in r.ribbons) {

let w = r.ribbons[k];

if (w.offsetX) {

w.x += map(noise(w.offsetX), 0, 1, -0.3, 0.3);

w.y += map(noise(w.offsetY), 0, 1, -0.3, 0.3);

w.offsetX += 0.002;

w.offsetY += 0.002;

}

}

}

// ------------------- Draw -------------------

function drawRibbon(r) {

// --- THETA BACKGROUND MICRO LAYER ---

let t = r.ribbons.theta;

if (t) {

push();

noStroke();

blendMode(ADD);

// faint halo

fill(t.hue, 30, 70, t.alpha * 0.3);

ellipse(t.x, t.y, t.size * 1.8, t.size * 1.8);

// core micro blob

fill(t.hue, 35, 80, t.alpha);

ellipse(

---

t.x,

t.y,

t.size + sin(frameCount * 0.006) * t.wobbleX,

t.size + cos(frameCount * 0.006) * t.wobbleY

);

pop();

}

// --- MIDGROUND WAVES ---

if (r.ribbons.alpha) drawWave(r.ribbons.alpha, true);

if (r.ribbons.beta) drawWave(r.ribbons.beta);

if (r.ribbons.gamma) drawWave(r.ribbons.gamma);

// --- DELTA ATMOSPHERIC DEPTH ---

let d = r.ribbons.delta;

if (d) {

push();

stroke(d.hue, 40, 70, d.alpha * 0.6);

strokeWeight(1.3);

for (let i = 0; i < 4; i++) {

line(

d.x,

d.y + i * 18 + sin(frameCount * 0.01 + i) * 20,

d.x + width,

d.y + i * 18

);

}

pop();

}

}

---

// ------------------- Wave -------------------

function drawWave(w, soft = false) {

push();

translate(w.x, w.y);

noFill();

for (let i = 0; i < w.length; i++) {

let y =

sin(i * w.frequency + frameCount * 0.01) *

w.amplitude *

noise(i * 0.05, frameCount * 0.002);

let a = w.alpha * map(i, 0, w.length, 1, 0);

if (soft) a *= 0.7;

stroke(w.hue, 80, 90, a);

strokeWeight(w.strokeWeight * map(i, 0, w.length, 0.5, 1));

point(i, y);

}

pop();

}

// ------------------- Sound -------------------

function playBrainSound() {

let vel = map(eegData.meditation, 0, 1, 0.25, 0.6);

let dur = map(eegData.beta, 0, 1, 0.06, 0.2);

synth.play(map(eegData.alpha, 0, 1, 200, 700), vel, 0, dur);

synth.play(map(eegData.beta, 0, 1, 400, 900), vel * 0.8, 0, dur * 0.8);

synth.play(map(eegData.theta, 0, 1, 150, 350), vel * 0.5, 0, dur * 1.3);

synth.play(map(eegData.delta, 0, 1, 60, 140), vel * 0.4, 0, dur * 1.6);

---

synth.play(map(eegData.gamma, 0, 1, 900, 1800), vel, 0, dur * 0.6);

}

// ------------------- HUD -------------------

function drawHUD() {

fill(0, 0, 100);

textSize(10);

textAlign(LEFT, TOP);

text(' üé® Living Painterly EEG Canvas', 10, 10);

text('Theta (indigo): micro background texture', 10, 26);

text('Alpha/Beta: painterly waves', 10, 40);

text('Delta: atmospheric depth', 10, 54);

if (!eegData.connected) {

fill(0, 0, 70);

text(' ‚ö† Using Simulated Data', 10, 72);

}

}

function windowResized() {

resizeCanvas(windowWidth, windowHeight);

background(0);

}
